    # TH (Tyrosine Hydroxylase) — Expert Analysis
    **Biological function.** TH catalyzes the rate-limiting step in catecholamine biosynthesis: conversion of L-tyrosine to L-DOPA using tetrahydrobiopterin (BH4), Fe²⁺, and O₂ as cofactors. L-DOPA is the obligate precursor to dopamine, norepinephrine, and epinephrine. The enzyme operates as a homotetramer with an N-terminal regulatory domain (containing the autoinhibitory Ser19/Ser31/Ser40 phosphosites — substrates for PKA, CaMKII, ERK1/2, and CDK5) and a C-terminal catalytic domain harboring the Fe²⁺ binding pocket. Activity is gated by feedback inhibition from catecholamine binding to the regulatory domain, BH4 availability, and phosphorylation-driven relief of autoinhibition. Expression is restricted to catecholaminergic neurons (substantia nigra pars compacta, VTA, locus coeruleus) and chromaffin cells of the adrenal medulla.
    **Transcript landscape.** The 14 annotated transcripts (8 protein-coding) reflect well-characterized human-specific alternative splicing in exons 1–2 that yields four major isoforms (hTH1–hTH4), differing in N-terminal regulatory domain length and phosphorylation kinetics. hTH1 and hTH2 are the dominant brain isoforms; hTH3/hTH4 carry additional 27- and 31-aa insertions absent from rodent orthologs — a critical caveat when extrapolating mouse Th biology to human disease. The 497-aa canonical isoform corresponds to hTH1.
    **Disease associations.** Biallelic loss-of-function TH variants cause autosomal recessive DOPA-responsive dystonia / Segawa syndrome and infantile parkinsonism (OMIM 605407) — Arg233His, Leu205Pro, and the promoter -71C>T variant are recurrent. Phenotype severity tracks residual enzymatic activity: <15% yields infantile encephalopathy, 15–40% yields the levodopa-responsive dystonic phenotype. TH is not a Mendelian Parkinson's gene, but nigral TH⁺ neuron loss is the defining pathological feature of idiopathic PD, and TH immunoreactivity is the standard quantitative endpoint for nigrostriatal degeneration in 6-OHDA, MPTP, and α-synuclein PFF models. Reduced striatal TH activity is also implicated in schizophrenia-associated dopaminergic dysregulation and ADHD pharmacogenomics (TH VNTR in intron 1).
    **Experimental recommendations.** For expression quantification, use isoform-discriminating primers spanning the exon 1–2 junction rather than pan-TH qPCR if human samples are involved — total TH mRNA can mask isoform shifts that alter phosphoregulation. For protein-level work, phospho-specific antibodies (pSer31, pSer40) report activity state more faithfully than total TH; pair with HPLC-ECD measurement of tissue DOPA/dopamine to confirm flux. In stereotaxic lesion or AAV-α-syn rodent models, stereological TH⁺ cell counts in SNc must be paired with striatal TH terminal density (optical densitometry) — terminals degenerate before somata, and soma counts alone underestimate early pathology. For variant functional characterization, recombinant expression in Sf9 or E. coli followed by L-DOPA production assay with BH4 cofactor is the standard; include thermal stability (DSF) since many disease variants are folding/stability mutants rather than catalytic-site lesions.
    **Clinical relevance.** TH-deficient patients are the cleanest example of "treatable neurotransmitter disease" — early L-DOPA/carbidopa initiation in Segawa syndrome produces near-complete phenotypic rescue, making newborn CSF neurotransmitter screening (HVA/5-HIAA ratio) high-yield in unexplained infantile dystonia. Gene therapy efforts (AAV2-AADC for AADC deficiency, Eladocagene exuparvovec, approved 2022) have established the regulatory and surgical playbook that AAV-TH or combined AAV-TH/GCH1/AADC strategies for PD are now leveraging in active trials.

